body:
>Write a component that wraps the Ant select component and injects a hidden select into the DOM that mirrors the Ant select.

I think the issue is that the Selenium tests aim to click on the select `option`s to alter the form values and go from there, so if we had our own secret select somewhere on the page, we'd have to fire changes in both directions.

@18epedersen Do you need to interact with the `select` (like fake clicks), or do you just need to read its values?

body_text:
Write a component that wraps the Ant select component and injects a hidden select into the DOM that mirrors the Ant select.

I think the issue is that the Selenium tests aim to click on the select options to alter the form values and go from there, so if we had our own secret select somewhere on the page, we'd have to fire changes in both directions.
@18epedersen Do you need to interact with the select (like fake clicks), or do you just need to read its values?
